HEADWORD: Campanularian
<hw>Cam*pan`u*la"ri*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>campanula</ets> a bell.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A hydroid of
the family <fam>Campanularid⟦ae⟧</fam>, characterized by having the
polyps or zooids inclosed in bell-shaped calicles or
hydrothec⟦ae⟧.</def>⟦br⟧
